<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12008m"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12008m">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12008m"> 8(m)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Nodier <font face="wake">D</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Mais, si je compare la meilleure langue qui ait &eacute;t&eacute; &eacute;crite au dix-huiti&egrave;me si&egrave;cle: celle de Voltaire ou plut&ocirc;t de Montesquieu, &agrave; la meilleure langue qui l&apos;ait &eacute;t&eacute; au dix-neuvi&egrave;me: celle de Nodier, de Hugo, d&apos;Anatole France, je vous avouerai que je pr&eacute;f&egrave;re la seconde: elle est ensemble moins s&egrave;che et plus rigoureuse. <br><font color="green">[But if I compare the best language written in the sixteenth century: that of Voltaire or rather of Montesquieu, to the best language written in the nineteenth: that of <mark>Nodier</mark>, Hugo, Anatole France, I have to admit that I prefer the latter: it is altogether less dry and more rigorous.]</font> <small> Jacques Boulenger &amp; Andr&eacute; Th&eacute;rive, <a name="SOIR" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#SOIR"><cite title="source">Les Soir&eacute;es du Grammaire-Club</cite></a> (1924) 130</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: The French writer, Charles Nodier (1780-1844). </mm> </dd></dl>
